# DigiOne — Marketing Brief & Campaign Foundation

> **Built from codebase research. Last updated: April 2026.**
> Use this document as the single source of truth for all copywriting, ads, social content, and pitch decks.

---

## 1. What Is DigiOne?

**DigiOne is India's all-in-one creator monetization platform.** It replaces the patchwork of tools (Instamojo + Linktree + Mailchimp + Gumroad + Canva) that Indian creators currently use, with a single integrated SaaS that covers every step of the creator business — from product creation to storefront to checkout to payout.

DigiOne is built specifically for the Indian market:
- All pricing is in **₹ (INR)**
- Payouts are settled to **Indian bank accounts** via PAN/KYC verification
- The payment infrastructure runs on **Cashfree**, the most popular Indian payment gateway among creators and SMBs

---

## 2. The Problem We Solve

Indian digital creators — educators, designers, developers, coaches, and content creators — face a fragmented monetization stack:

| Problem | Current "Solution" | DigiOne Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Selling digital products | Instamojo / Gumroad | Native product manager with instant checkout |
| Link-in-bio page | Linktree / Milkshake | Fully branded, custom-domain bio pages |
| Product landing pages | Carrd / Notion | Drag-free Landing Page Builder |
| Running promotions | Mailchimp / manual DMs | Built-in coupons, affiliates, referrals, Auto DM |
| Getting paid | Manual NEFT requests | KYC-verified auto-settlement to bank accounts |
| Analytics | Google Analytics (complex) | Native revenue + sales dashboard |

**The result:** creators spend more time managing tools than making content. DigiOne collapses this entire stack into one login.

---

## 3. Target Personas

### Primary: The Indian Solo Creator
- **Age:** 22–38
- **Platform:** Instagram, YouTube, Twitter/X
- **What they sell:** Notion templates, Figma files, online courses, ebooks, presets, code boilerplates
- **Pain:** "I lose sales because my checkout process is broken / confusing."
- **Aspiration:** "I want to earn ₹1L/month from digital products without hiring a tech team."

### Secondary: The Educator / Coach
- **What they sell:** Structured courses, 1:1 sessions, cohort programs
- **Pain:** "I have 10,000 followers but no system to sell to them."
- **Aspiration:** "I want Gumroad-level simplicity but designed for Indian buyers."

### Tertiary: The Agency / Indie Dev
- **What they sell:** Design assets, SaaS templates, code packages
- **Pain:** "Every tool I use charges in USD and takes international payment fees."
- **Aspiration:** Rupee-native payments, no FX hassle.

---

## 4. Platform Feature Map

### Products
Creators can list and manage multiple types of digital products:
- **Digital Files** — PDFs, ZIPs, videos, audio
- **Courses** — Structured learning content
- **Templates** — Design or code templates
- **Other** — Custom digital items

Each product has: pricing (INR), thumbnail, description, publish/draft state, and direct checkout support.

### Sites (6 Site Types)
The most powerful differentiator. One platform, six ways to sell:

| Site Type | What it is |
|---|---|
| **Main Store** | Full e-commerce storefront listing all products |
| **Link in Bio** | Premium, mobile-first bio page (replaces Linktree) |
| **Single Page / Landing Page** | High-converting sales page for a single product |
| **Blog** | Content-driven SEO site with product CTAs |
| **Payment Link** | Instant one-click checkout link |
| **Builder App** | Custom drag-and-drop page builder |

The Link in Bio editor and Single Page editor are full-screen, split-screen experiences with live preview panel (mobile/tablet/desktop modes), collapsible tab sidebar, real-time theme customization, and SEO metadata control.

### Marketing Suite
Built-in growth tools that eliminate the need for third-party apps:

- **Auto DM** — Instagram-style automated direct message flows
- **Automation** — Rule-based marketing triggers
- **Coupons** — Discount codes with usage limits
- **Affiliates** — Partner referral system
- **Referrals** — Customer-to-customer referral engine
- **Lead Capture** — Lead magnet forms and list building
- **Community** — Creator community engagement tools

### Analytics & Money
- Revenue dashboard with 30-day charts
- Per-product sales tracking
- Real-time order feed ("Live" badge with pulse animation)
- Earnings breakdown and payout history

### Payouts & KYC
- PAN-linked identity verification
- Bank account settlement (IFSC/account number)
- Compliance-grade review pipeline (pending → verified → rejected)
- Funds withdrawal once KYC is verified

### Upsell Pages
Shareable checkout links that include optional add-on products at checkout. Increase average order value by 20–40%.

---

## 5. Key Differentiators

### 1. India-First, Not India-Adapted
Most competing platforms (Gumroad, Kajabi, Podia) are built for US creators and adapted for India. DigiOne is designed from day 1 for Indian creators — INR native, Cashfree integration, PAN-KYC payout system, bank account settlement.

### 2. Six Site Types in One Account
Competitors give you one type of page. DigiOne gives you six. A creator can run a Link-in-Bio, a blog, a sales page, and a main storefront — all under the same login, same branding, same analytics.

### 3. Marketing Automation Built In
No need for ConvertKit, ManyChat, or Mailchimp. Auto DM, referrals, affiliates, and lead capture are native features, not integrations.

### 4. Premium Editor Experience
The editor UI rivals Webflow and Framer in quality — live preview, device switching, collapsible sidebar, undo/redo, theme tokens — yet stays accessible to non-technical creators.

### 5. Zero-Friction Checkout
Payment links and upsell pages eliminate friction. Buyers see a clean, branded checkout. Creators share one link. That's it.

